  <title>equivalent entity</title>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>Entity corresponding to the transfer of a H+ ion in a neutralization reaction, of an electron in a redox reaction, or to a magnitude of charge number equal to 1 in ions. Examples: 1/2H2SO4, 1/5KMnO4, 1/3Fe3+.</text>
